<h3>Features</h3>

<ol>
      <li>WorldTime2000 is self extracting setup program, not a ZIP file. Just click + install</li>
      <li>Windows Install/Uninstall from control panel feature </li>
      <li>Alarms with optional messages can be set for displayed locations </li>
      <li>Over 400 built-in locations including DST details This includes cities and time zones</li>
      <li>Font support - choose and font, point size and style to display times
      <li>Sound support - choose your own sounds for time events and alarms or turn them off
      <li>Wallpaper support added - choose any bitmaps for the window background. Just like the windows desktop
      <li>Text will automatically resize itself to the width of the window </li>
      <li>Text and background colors user definable </li>
      <li>An animated spinning globe. It doesn't do anything, but it looks good! </li>
      <li>Floating tooltips give you information on locations
      <li>Right mouse button ( context ) menus</li>
      <li>HTML help. That means help looks and acts just like a web page </li>
      <li>Multi-threaded support - should be less demanding resource wise, and take advantage of all those running dual processor Win NT/2000 systems
      <li>Locations can be viewed, arranged on screen, modified and deleted </li>
      <li>Display preferences are saved ( window details, colors, toolbars etc ) </li>
      <li>Time is adjusted according to the Daylight Savings rules for that location </li>
      <li>30 min and 1 hour increments from GMT </li>
      <li>Select between 12 or 24 hour time </li>
      <li>Home location's time zone set automatically. Home can be changed to any name of your liking </li>
      <li>You get to see your name on the display when you <strong>register</strong> </li>
</ol>


